content.question: public void conditionalTest(int a, int b) { if ((a > 0) && (b > 0)) { if (a > b) System.out.println("A"); else System.out.println("B"); } else if ((b < 0) || (a < 0)) System.out.println("C"); else System.out.println("D"); } What is printed as a result of the call conditionalTest(3, -2)?

skill.text: 3.A: Determine the result or output based on statement execution order in an algorithm.
